article.description: Jr. Clay registered 18 points and dished off five assists as Tennessee Tech defeated Morehead State 71-59 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Clay scores 18 as Tennessee Tech beats Morehead State, 71-59
article.linkText: Clay scores 18 as Tennessee Tech beats Morehead State, 71-59
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- Jr. Clay registered 18 points and dished off five assists as Tennessee Tech defeated Morehead State 71-59 on Thursday night. Tujautae Williams had 12 points for Tennessee Tech (5-15, 2-5 Ohio Valley Conference). Keishawn Davidson added 12 points and six assists. Darius Allen had seven rebounds. Tyzhaun Claude scored a season-high 20 points for the Eagles (9-11, 3-4). Jordan Walker added 11 points. Djimon Henson had 11 points. The Golden Eagles evened the season series against the Eagles with the win. Morehead State defeated Tennessee Tech 83-72 on Jan. 4. Tennessee Tech matches up against Eastern Kentucky at home on Saturday. Morehead State plays Jacksonville State on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
